title.narrative: FACILITY HEALTH

description.narrative: Increased capacity of health facilities to deliver a package of high impact health interventions for mothers, newborns and under 5 children with special focus on gender equality and the most vulnerable in all 13 districts by 2018, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Polio Eradication. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved and equitable use of high-impact maternal and child health intervention from pregnancy to adolescence and promotion of health behaviours

title.narrative: Increased capacity of health facilities to deliver a package of high impact health interventions for mothers, newborns and under 5children with special focus on gender equality and the most vulnerable in all 13 districts by 2018

description.narrative: Four high impact Special Baby Care Units (SBCUs) continued to provide quality 24/7 services, saving over 3,530 sick newborns' lives in 2019. Introduction of perinatal death surveillance and response, institutionalization of quarterly review and supportive supervision, and operationalization of newly developed standard operating procedures for sick newborns ensured continuous quality improvement. The nationwide scale-up of SBCUs is underway and will provide increased capacity to health facilities to deliver health interventions for mothers, newborns and under 5s. A new central cold store was commissioned and 220 solar refrigerators were installed across the country, expanding cold chain coverage. | Status:Met | As-of Date:05/02/2020
